RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MAY 22, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 22, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 Accredited Arkansas, Louisiana, and Texas Bred Prefe rred.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GALLANT STAR settled off the pace from the four path, was allowed to relax until the half mile pole, was given the cue and responded well and started closing from the outside, circled his rivals through the turn, had his aim on the in the leader in the stretch, collared that foe by the sixteenth pole and proceeded to drew away with a game win. OPTIMISTIC shuffled back after the break and settled well off the pace, started chasing the eventual winner after the half mile pole, followed that foe through the turn was three wide in the stretch and was kept to task, closing strong, couldn't beat the winner but was second best. SHARK HARBOR showed natural speed and went to the front willingly, showed the way until the half mile pole, was joined by an outside contender at the half mile pole, matched strides into the lane, and weakened late. CAYMANS COBRA stalked the early pace while racing three wide, was rated just off the leaders hip until the half mile marker, was given the cue and urged through the turn was in front for a few strides at the five sixteenth pole but then was joined by the early leader to his inside, battled, was run down by an outside attacker and tired mid stretch. MR. PRIORITY was off slow, and raced from off the pace , angled down to the rail and saved ground, but to no avail. CORVETTE SPIRIT was never involved. ROCKDALE was sent to the lead along the rail, was quickly joined by an outside competitor and matched strides with that one while attending the pace, gave way at the five sixteenth pole and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Priority
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, well off pace, saved ground, mild finish

ENTRY.NAME: Shark Harbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, led, challenged at the 1/2, matched 1/4, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Gallant Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 4w, moved 1/2, circled turn, cleared 16th, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Caymans Cobra
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 3w, rated, cue 1/2, briefly led, matched, tired

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANICLUDE bumped start with GRAHAM'S CRUISER, ducked to the rail set the early pace, stayed on the rail the whole race and driving finish by drawing off at the end. DOUBLE PRIORITY broke out of the gate first, stalked ANTICLUDE one to two lengths back 2 wide, finished strong 3 lengths off the win. BOSSHOG THEM DUKES ran 3 wide the entire race, off pace from leaders, ran flat no kick on the home stretch. GRAHAM 'S CRUISER had a bumped start from ANTICLUDE, stalked BOSSHOG THEM DUKES the entire race no drive at the home stretch. VALIANT DEFENDER broke slow trailed 5 wide the whole race with a late kick at the end to place 5th. DA GOLD ROOM good break, dueled GRAHAM'S CRUISER 3 wide, then faded at the one sixteenth pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Aniclude
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, set early pace on the rail

ENTRY.NAME: Da Gold Room
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide entire race, faded mid stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 71. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 22 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUTE DINERO QUEEN broke sharp was angled towards the rail into the four path, was quickly joined by rivals along the inside, smartly rated a bit staying just off the pace, matched strides with an inside foe past the half, when cued she drew away from her challenger on her inside, advanced past the early leader on the inside still in the three path. battled into the stretch but drew off as she pleased and was dominate this race. SHEZA SALTY GAL sent for the lead and secured the rail spot, set the pace until she was joined by her pressuring outside rivals, matched strides with the eventual winner at the three eighths pole, battled through the turn and into the lane but retreated after the sixteenth and settled for second. HOPEITSMYLUCKYDAY was pushed to the front, drew along side the eventual winner and matched strides with that foe while racing in between her and her opposition racing on the rail, was urged to stay with that set but tired, was still able to secure third. CECE WAVE backed off the speed and rated in hands along the rail, launched a bid at the three eights pole but to no avail. RUN NATALIE RUN was no menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Cece Wave
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated, off pace, rail, settled in hands, cued 3/8, no avail

ENTRY.NAME: Sheza Salty Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, sent, led, set pace, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Hopeitsmyluckyday
ENTRY.OWNER: Hodges Phyllis J and Schneider Randolph

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAVIAR RESOLUTION settled off the pace early on while racing in the six path, was asked and improved position at the half mile marker drawing beside the early leaders, continued to be urged, applied pressure to her inside rivals through the turn, was in a three way battle down the stretch and past the last sixteenth of a mile where she put the rest away and went on for the win. JOANIE GAL sent early to be forwardly placed, gently took back and rated just off the early speed, stalked that leader and was joined by an outside attacker at he half mile pole, these two drew along the side of the early leader and launched a three battle into the furlong ground, and tired. Though she was pressured and battled in between two competitor through the lane JOANIE GAL ran a game race and was up for second. CUSTOM MAIDEN vied for the early lead, secured the rail and set the pace, showed the way into the furlong ground faded late. SIMPLE SUNDAY raced mid pack early on from the three path, was urged in between horses and improved position into the second flight of horses, maintained position through the turn edged out in the upper stretch into the five path, was encouraged with clear racing room, but to no avail. BEAUX TOX was off slow and while racing wide was no factor. WHO DAT GREY saved ground along the rail, was urged to move up into the second flight on the rail inside of other rivals, was placed well through the turn but faltered. LIL HOT TODDY was no menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Custom Maiden
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, rail, set the pace, battled, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Joanie Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, rated, 3w, between 5-16th, 3 way battle, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Caviar Resolution
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 6w, moved 1/2, 4w, joined leaders7-16th, 3wuppr, up

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 5 7 1/2F Turf CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on th e main track at one mile and seventy yards) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RICKY RIGHT was four wide going into the first turn, pulled against the bit getting to the front, took the lead at the six furlong pole, angled closer to the rail, entered the top of the stretch in front was slightly pressured by a closing rival before he drew away gamely in the deep stretch. RONALDS GATSBY raced off the pace along the rail, gained ground at the half mile pole, shifted out five wide while chasing the leader into the furlong ground, where he was putting pressure on the eventual winner but could not secure the win and had to settle for second best today. STAR READY stalked the early pace from the rail, improved position while being two wide moved in between foes, was in contention by the quarter pole but did not have enough today. CLEARLY A JET raced mid pack while taking a ground saving trip, maintained that position through out and finished with a mild bid. FLAT OUT FABIO showed little. ADDISONS WARRIOR was forwardly placed and faded. VERO CAMPIONE was no factor. OWEN THE ICE MAN was never involved. TRIPLE trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Ronalds Gatsby
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, rail, moved 1/2, 5w, chased, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Clearly a Jet
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, saved ground, maintained position

ENTRY.NAME: Star Ready
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, rail, 2w, btwn, ground saving trip, no late kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 22, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NO WHITE FLAGS stalked the early pace setter while he rated waiting for the cue, happily took command and by the last sixteenth and drew off gamely. LUNAR MODULE battled for the lead, set the pace from the inside and gave way late. HARDCORE FOLKLORE raced along the rail in the middle of the pack, advanced along the rail while improving position, started to drift out at the five sixteenth pole and drifted out further in the stretch but did not have enough to overcome the first two finishers and settled for third. STOCKPILER settled into the middle of the pack, maintained his position. FAR BEYOND showed little. BREAD WINNER was never involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Hardcore Folklore
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, rail, drifted out stretch not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Stockpiler
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, maintained position through out,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 22 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SONO broke sharp and smartly took back a bit and rated, was asked at the quarter pole and drew off with a nice turn of foot and was the easy winner. HOOSIER was off a bit slow and settled well off the pace, started to gain ground and closed after the half mile pole, was in full stride by the sixteenth pole and was up for second. CALICOCO raced mid pack, patiently waited, then closed well. KING OF CONTRABAND was off a tough and slow and made a mild bid late. PITCH AND RUN was never a factor. REVERENT showed little. DIAL UNCLE JOEY was never involved. RISKTAKER off slow, mild gain. LOUISIANA FLASH was forwardly placed, but tired. SON CARLOS vied, led, then stoppe.

ENTRY.NAME: Hoosier
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off the pace, asked 1/2, closed well, up for second

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 8 5F Turf CR: 94. Allowance Purse 30000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MAY 22, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 22, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUKE OF CARTHANIA stalked the early leaders, improved position then out finished the rest. HE'S A BOMB stalked while racing on the rail, maintained position through out and was up for second. MEN OF KYLE was of a touch slow but gained ground at each marker and finished well. NATE'S WAY was forwardly placed and faltered. OLD HOMESTEAD off slow and was never a threat. MEANT FOR ME raced mid pack early then tired. PEPPER JACK showed little. COUNT DE MONET flashed early speed.
